    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a lost container claim, you must have the Bill of Lading (B/L), which serves as a contract of carriage and a title document, as well as the commercial invoice. If the container is completely lost, the carrier's confirmation of non-delivery or a \"shortage/loss\" claim report is crucial evidence. The insurance company will then review these documents to process the claim against the policy the seller purchased.",
